video_title: Return of His Majesty | DramaBox
text: Guys, if you don't want spoilers, please ignore this comment.I saw the first ad, and I ended up getting hooked, because it caught my curiosity, but I definitely don't consider it something worth watching. You may have noticed, but the script is extremely prolix, redundant and convoluted, and they turn what could be an entertaining short film into a more than 2 hours content. I watched the whole thing, and I hope this comment helps at least someone not to waste their time.Basically, the protagonist spends almost all his time hiding the fact that he is the emperor, and his subordinates help him jn the farce, and pretend it too. The story is extremely drawn out, they practically make the dialogues repeat themselves all the time to extend the scenes as much as possible, in addition to dragging out a lot in several plots just to reinforce the cruelty of the villains. The Emperor always defends the poor and says that his ex-fianc√©e will regret everything and that the Shaws will pay. His ex-fianc√©e's sister is good and ends up being the emperor's romantic partner. After approximately 1 hour and 50 minutes of the story, he finally reveals himself to be the emperor and the villains "regret" all they did right away. His ex-fianc√©e tries to apologize and begs to be made the Empress, but it is obviously too late and he has already seen her true colors. So, after an unnecessarily long scene of him lecturing the villains, he declares that they must be executed. At the end, it shows him back in his palace and he declares that he wants to create an anti-corruption task force to prevent others from abusing the people like the Shaws did, and then the story ends.It would have been a fun watch if the script wasn't designed to drag out the narrative as much as possible to suck the viewer's money.

text: It's hard to forgive someone you truly love when they backstabbed you and put you in prison. He lost what, 3 years of his life in prison? Then to top it off, she hid his child away from him. She would've kept doing it if the child was not sick. Only when the child was stuck that the secret was out in the open. Yes, help the child to get better but the chances of reconciliation is 0. I wouldn't want to get back together with someone who chose her family (her parents and/or siblings) over me, either, then keep a child hidden, knowing full well that it's our child. No thank you! In most Asian families, sons are favored over daughters bc sons will carry on the family name while daughters will get married and carry her husband's name, thus, she is no longer her family's daughter. That is how most Asians see daughters. That's why parents will go all out for their sons and leave their daughters in the dust, doing the bare minimum for them. Some parents in third world countries won't even allow their daughters to attend school bc they're jealous that if they fund their daughters education, she'll get married and help her husband and his family have a better life.

video_title: [MULTI SUB] Forgiveness for Love„ÄêFull„ÄëAfter backstabbing my ex, he became a bossy CEO | Drama Zone
text: ‚Äã@stephanien6237 (Spoilers Below!) Well, I can see the story from both of their points of view. To be clear, I'm not condoning the actions of either lead, but I can understand the drive behind them. I'll focus on the ML's side since it seems you already empathized well with the FL. She shattered his heart and put him through hell. He even had a line that was something like wanting to 'bring her into hell with him' because he was still feeling tormented by her betrayal of their love. Her metaphorically backstabbing him by giving false testimony and having him sent to jail (where he's almost truly stabbed to death) for a murder he did not commit, was completely unexpected to him. He never knows until near the end of the story that she did it to save her mom. As they start crossing paths again I can see his deep bitterness, but also his growing desperation for her love- to have her show that at least some part of what he thought they once shared was real. The ML is not inherently cruel (the flashbacks show the huge contrast in demeanor), circumstances have influenced him to grow hard, cold, bitter, and ruthless. Throughout the story his inner turmoil is apparent, at least it was to me. His resolve for revenge softens over time despite his hurts. That, his desperation for her to love him back, and his eventual decision to forgive everything, indicates how strongly he feels about her.The FL also continues to hide and then lie about their child (I can understand that she's afraid of the daughter being taken away or being used against her, but I can also see the argument that telling him at some point sooner could have greatly sped up her medical care because the ML could afford it. So covering up the truth for so long technically hurts the daughter as well as the ML, especially since the daughter wants a father and already gets along well with the ML).The FL herself never blames the ML. She's never stopped loving him, but she holds that back and doesn't show it. When the ML agrees to walk away and never see her again, she regrets it and says to herself, "Even if it's hate, I don't want to lose you". Though at that point he doesn't hate her anymore, that's why he lets her go.At the end, it seemed that things were heading in the direction of mending and, had the FL not had a terminal illness, the two of them and their daughter could have healed emotional wounds over time and been able to grow into a happy family.Life was hard for both of them. Some of that instigated by outside forces and circumstances, some through misunderstandings, and some due to their own perceptions, decisions, and actions. I just wished for everybody's suffering to ease.I thought the FL's suicide seemed a bit contrived because it felt out of character, but that's another discussion.

video_title: [MULTI SUB] Forgiveness for Love„ÄêFull„ÄëAfter backstabbing my ex, he became a bossy CEO | Drama Zone
text: Tho the ending is so heartbreaking and make me crying a river but i am very very satisfied with this kind of ending!!!! The best retribution for a man like bo hanshi is like this, has no a future and cant amend his sins to that person he owe to the most!! A dead of his victim is best kind of revenge as he has no chance to show his apology, his sincerity that he's really regret it, and his way in atoning his sins. However he make those efforts, the feel cant reach to the dead person as they're already living in the different world. But unfortunately, the writer doesnt show us how qiao yu's mom got killed. As the culprit is jiang wan, the vicious girl who will do anything to make bo hanshi marry her. Also there is no scene how bo hanshi will explaining to bo xiangshi (his daughter) about her mom is already died. As i believe the big contribution is bo hanshi, he make qiao yu drank so much alcohol to humaliate her and it lead her to hv a late stage of liver cancer. But when i know that bo hanshi also has an ulterior motive for came to qiao family back then, i think that this drama had a dark plot. text: I think most of us are used to the same old toxic abuse stories where the male lead is unforgivably abusive to the female lead for years and then gets a ridiculous, unearned and undeserved ‚Äúhappy ending‚Äù usually without any actual work or remorse on his side. Bonus points if he takes the knife of forgiveness instead of actually having to work to atone for his sins. üòÇThis drama, although still having the FL stay and suffer for 5 years, actually spent 3/4 of the drama (from about 41:00 on) realizing he was wrong, showing honest remorse, having to deal with the fact that the FL doesn‚Äôt love him and may get with another guy, and having to work slowly to a) respect her and b) atone before he gets a second chance. And for once the male lead isn‚Äôt an arrogant controlling AH for the last 3/4 of the drama! Refreshing. We are so used to the usual where 90% of drama is pure abuse followed by the male lead ‚Äúrealizing he was wrong‚Äù and calling it a ‚Äúmisunderstanding‚Äù followed by a barely-there apology and then 2 minutes later he takes the knife of forgiveness and all his sins are supposedly magically erased. üòÇüòÇüòÇ I hate those. It was nice to see a ML actually show some honest character development.

video_title: [MULTI SUB] My Ex-husband's Regret„ÄêFull„ÄëStupid women live for love, now I live for myself|Drama Zone
text: Ps. Can you remind me why he loves her? I‚Äôm asking seriously because I can absolutely understand why he would feel guilt and shame for mistreating her when he finds out the truth (even though he never once felt bad for mistreating her during their 5 year marriage‚Äîwhich suggests he is not a decent human being). But given that he never actually got to know her, why did he love her? I feel like they never really had a chance to connect as people. He just was an arrogant AH, she divorced him and left, he finally found out the truth (something he never bothered to figure out before then), and suddenly he feels bad so he thinks he now loves her? Or maybe he missed all the comforts she gave him that he didn‚Äôt realize (like the soup). That‚Äôs not love.

video_title: [MULTI SUB] My Ex-husband's Regret„ÄêFull„ÄëStupid women live for love, now I live for myself|Drama Zone

text: I watched another version of this a while ago and remember enjoying it. This one is off to a really good start. I like the way these actors are playing the roles. Very dynamic.The ML's doctor friend is definitely the smartest, attentive and most insightful one in the bunch. I love how he sits back and just enjoys the show going on around him. ü§£1:53:10 I'm scared to say it and jinx it (knocking on wood) but I've loved everything about this drama so far. Everything the leads has done is exactly what I'd hoped they would do. It's been unbelievably satisfying and entertaining. What worries me is that there's so much more left to go, which means they can screw the story up tremendously. It's extremely rare that I haven't been let down. This version of the story has been following the other version I saw closely enough but in better detail. It's like a major upgrade of the script (and I really liked the other version already as it was). The runtime here is a lot longer but it definitely doesn't feel slow at all. The pacing, surprisingly, is just right. I hope like hell this continues to be great and doesn't become another disappointment.2:57:25 Uh oh! I think they may be heading in a direction of the first and only thing I may end up disliking about this drama - a dumb ass noble sacrifice!!! I hope they don't do it. Writing this good doesn't need to be tainted by such stupidity. She should know better than to make decisions for him. BUT, the headline for this video makes it seem like it's coming. UGH! Say it isn't so!! This drama has literally been perfect so far for me.3:00:00 This FL and this drama sure is doing its best not to let us down! Seeing her try to talk him through the loss without telling him what's going on, trying to make sure he won't blindly follow her was just so ON POINT! It's not the normal noble idiocy. It's in line with the behavior of the FL all along, which is really all I was hoping for. Lord I LOVE this dang drama!!!

video_title: [MULTI SUB] Blind in Love„ÄêFull„ÄëBlind CEO and Disguised Wife, True Love in Conspiracy | Drama Zone
text: 5 out of 5 stars. Comedy/Drama. Nit much sizzling romance but it's a story of ML who is blind via emotional trauma and a spunky FL and both stubborn and opposites of each other. ML starts off rude, arrogant and aloof and thinks she's like all women, vain and greedy for money. Of course people around him constantly put him and his blindness as being undesirable and useless. FL is direct and impulsive being bullied into marriage as he's a higher social status and rich. The father is being hostage as he's in a coma and they use him to extort money from her.The two slowly start to trust each other though ML iis suspicious of her all the time. His assistant provides comedy relief. There's an illegitimate heir conspiring to take over the company and force ML out. It's a good and satisfying end.

this was for me a waste of time. the story was ridiculously abusive. metal and physical..ml obviously had his mother psychopathic traits. He was emotionally abusive. He was ready to prostitute out the female lead for me. He had no character nothing of what a man should be.Narcissist in anyways. There was nothing about him that one should love. Unless you like being emotionally abused, handed around and being used. The female lead, apart from being a doormat, which is every man's dream, she had a good heart. Her character is one that is portrayed as an insecure unloved person. Who took the crap that was handed out to her by the male lead and his mother and his Wife and her sister. She was placid and emotionally weak. It's like there are no other men in the world except for the main lead. She obviously did not know what love meant. Just like the male lead.The impact of a drama like this where it is psychological abuse can't be seen as a romance , why do I say that because this drama highlights what a woman should not put up with and what a man who is using a woman looks like. So really this should be a lesson to the women out there that this is what you avoid at all costs, because no man is worth it, or in some cases, no woman. Female lead obviously has no self-love nor does she know how to respect herself. Although she did try to leave him and that is how this drama should have ended. The male lead mother had an unnatural hold over her son. The son was weak and had no backbone to oppose his mother who was an utterly disgusting woman that used disgusting ways to hurt anyone that came into contact with her son that she did not like. She was a criminal, but she did not pay the price for her criminal activities.At the end that they should get married is a messed up scenario. To get married to a man who emotionally used and abused you means he has already done it once and got away with it by saying," I'm sorry" he will be fully aware that he can do this as much as he likes to you because he can get away with it.

video_title: [MULTI SUB] The Professor My Husband„ÄêFull„ÄëFortune says you're the one, so says my heart | Drama Zone
text: A very sweet, gentle and lovely drama. Perhaps a little on the long side as the story progresses very slowly with little skinship between the leads, no high tension points, no negative characters (except one jealous classmate but that character was ineffective) and a dreamlike, meandering pace. The ML is a lovely 'green flag'. The FL a sweet innocent girl with cutsie little girlfriends who stand by her. The family on both sides are supportive & loving. You could safely let you children watch this one. No physical violence, no physical bullying of the FL (some cyber but that's sorted immediately), no love rivals, just a gentle slow burn story with two sweet leads.
